commit_message:
Made logbooks deletable

book FK in logentry is now set to on delete cascade
Stop approved logentries from being deleted
Added some tests for log entries
Fixed redirect to index, instead of books on book create
updates to admin page, books and logentry
Changes to some forms, and models so that category is on logbooks
Added some login and signup tests
Add missing logbook id and fix back button
Edited the nav bar to include link to FAQ
Un-hardcoded links and switched to logbook ids for url
Un-hardcoded links and switched to logbook ids for url

Updated site to have a front page with icons

Is someone able to ensure my links are correct
Fixed formatting done by the auto-formatter
Added views and front end for logbook/entry forms

Merge branch 'supervisor' into modelViews

Conflicts:
	logbook/templates/base.html
	logbook/templates/index.html
	logbook/templates/logentry.html
	logbook/views.py

Added delete and sorting to logbook/entries

NOTE: supervisor code messed up until merge

Made some changes to what supervisors see

Allowed supervisors to see the logbooks from which students want a log
entry approved, the url for the logbooks depend on a migration currently
in the master branch which includes a slug field in the logbook model.
Could even load the log entries directly into the page and have drop
downs which have the entry information requiring approval, will discuss.

Made some adjustments to the html files

Changed the sidebars as well as altering the url of logbook links
Updated views and urls to work with the slugs

Updated logbook model

Added a slug field, so that we can generate user urls, based on the name
of the logbook.

Made style changes to the website.

Also made some changes to the links to the different logbooks and the
log entries in the logbooks

Added logentry page

Added log entry view and a regex patterned url as well as the
logentry.html file to the templates folder. LogEntry.html has templating
to show only the most important fields in the log entry to keep things
simple.
Fixed something left behind in index.html from testing

Made some changes to pages

Added some javascript to index.html (I can't javascript, so someone plz
get it to work). Added the logentry template and added some content to
the profile template.

Moved repeated code in forms.py into a base class

Repeated code in SignupForm and SupervisorSignupForm moved to
SignupFormBase
Fixed issue with adding logentries with negative time

Editted Looks and Checks

Fixed check on delete action so that books containing pending items wont
be deleted
Fixed Error Messages on form submit

Added ability to finalise a book

Allows students to finalise the book at end of semester. Added a test to
not add logbooks if there exists an active log book with the same
organisation. Edited layouts and some buttons
Fixed sorting in logentry and updated styling of reset password pages

Pushing work to remote

So i can work on it on PC, changes entirely to do with getting
autocomplete to work for supervisors
Changes to font size added search to match main site
Added ability to change password for logged in user

Moved datetime widget data to log entry.html

Stops each page loading the content despite it only being used on one
page
Added fonts and updated layout of some divs
Added ability for users to change passwords

Updated accordion action

Addition of <form> inside of the accordion div, caused it to not work.
Moved form to wrap around accordion div to solve the issue. Moved
Summary information to panel-footer

Updated urls

Removed auth urls from main urls and selected which to add to
logbook.urls

Overrode login and logout from auth

Placed logbook.urls above auth.urls, so login and logout remain the same
but password_reset works
Added template files for reset password

Updated registration

Allowed users to request a new activation link, if their old one expires

Made sidebar position absolute

Stops it from moving down with the page

Edited main css style

Styled footer and added the fonts which are being used in the new guild
volunteering website

Some updates to layout and styling

Designed to make site match new volunteering site
Added some of the registration code

Added message to supervisor if no hours to approve

Also made changes to the buttons on mobile, and added a declineAll if
supervisor is being spammed (subject to change)

Conflicts:
	logbook/forms.py
Made some crappy forms, mostly just made to reserve names
Added organisation FKEY to logbook model

Added a profile and changed templating

Included a base.html template which holds the general look of the site,
and other pages can choose their own title, as whether they want a
sidebar and what to put in the body
Signup form now checks if a user already exists

Added comments for admin file

Added further checks on the clear logbook view, so that it doesnt clear
logbooks if there are unexported logbooks still in the database.

Added mass emailing of different user groups

Admin view gives option for mass emailing users, who are either students
or supervisors.

Updated Admin Export

Added in glyphicons (tick or cross) to visually show, all information
has been removed from the database. Restricted the ability to 'clear'
database of finalised logbooks UNTIL all un-exported data has been
removed. Allowed admins to export all organisations at once which then
outputs a csv file with every organisation in it.
Editted field names, emailing and form submission

Added view for search bar

Had to create a context processor so that the form for the bar is
rendered into all the pages

Fixed critical documentation

Probably a good idea, otherwise no one could ever read anything. DO SAME
FOR ADMIN

Removed top search bar

Only have the bottom search bar, simplifies the toolbar

Add supervisor form

Added form to add log entry so students can create a temporary
supervisor, and guild volunteering can then verify that supervisor at a
later date

Updated outputting

Only includes log entries where the supervisor has been approved.
See diff for more changes to outputting

Restricted website access

If user is not added to any group either supervisor or lbuser they could
still access site!!
Allowed for clearing of finalised logbooks
Fixed admin outputting and error checking on form

Fixed some layout stuff

fixed datetime widget for mobile and fixed sidebar being rendered
